cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the development of calculi for various logics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as team-based logics are used in multi-agent systems and game theory, which are relevant to AI. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as team-based logics can be used in collaborative learning scenarios. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper presents complete axiomatizations for various team-based logics. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the development of calculi, which can be relevant to programming language semantics.
